# Docker after changes

Whenever you modify files in this repository as part of the work (code, static assets, Docker config, env examples, etc.), **restart the stack** from the project root so the running container matches the tree:

```bash
cd /home/jaybird/jayprograms/dashbird && docker compose up -d --build
```

Use `docker compose down && docker compose up -d --build` if a full recycle is needed. Do this **after** your edits for that turn are done, not only on request.
